CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 22, 1941, pg. 9, reads: "Had Good Time on Visit - Lovely Lena Horne spent a few days in Pittsburgh last week. When guest at the smart Synchronettes Valentine party Friday evening, Photographer Harris snapped this charming photo.  She left for Washington Saturday to join Charlie Barnett's orchestra.  While in city she was guest of her dad, Ted Horne."
TitMainTitle: Lena Horne seated on radiator, in club
